'''Johannes Mollerup''' (born 3 December 1872 in [[Nyborg]]; died 27 June 1937) was a Danish mathematician.<ref>http://www.litteraturpriser.dk/hbog/dblm.htm</ref><ref>[http://denstoredanske.dk/It,_teknik_og_naturvidenskab/Matematik_og_statistik/Matematikkens_historie/Johannes_Mollerup Johannes Mollerup]. Gyldendal – Den Store Danske.</ref>'

Mollerup studied at the [[University of Copenhagen]], and received his doctorate in 1903.

Together with [[Harald Bohr]], he developed the [[Bohr–Mollerup theorem]] which provides an easy [[Characterization (mathematics)|characterization]] of the [[gamma function]].

